summary: In this context, 1,1,2-trichloroethene (TCE) is discussed in relation to groundwater contamination, while dichlorobis(ethylenediamine)rhodium(III) is not mentioned at all. There is no direct or indirect relationship established between TCE and dichlorobis(ethylenediamine)rhodium(III) in the provided information, as the focus is solely on TCE's environmental impact and its plume characteristics.
